Remarks. Five species are recognized in this region (B.L. Fisher and M.A. Smith, unpublished); four were examined in the present study. Species known from the Malagasy region have a distinct spine or tooth on each dorsolateral petiolar margin, and are easily separated from other genera by this character. However, males of a species (morphospecies 
A. blf-pat
) from Aldabra do not have lateral teeth on the petiole. In addition, the male of a species (morphospecies 
A. blf-goo
) from Madagascar is not yet known; given the morphology of workers, males might also lack lateral teeth on the petiole.
